{
  "stem": "3964.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Not only did I say one parsha, but I recited the whole sidra of the Torah portion, which was read at my bar mitzvah, which was Kedoshim.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we have Torah as well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So it was a really momentous experience for me, having learned and studied, and then being able to decide the-- the whole Torah portion of my bar mitzvah part.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was a good experience-- wonderful experience.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But our religious life, our life at home, did not change at all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Our faith in God, our belief in better days to come, the optimism my father always had, prevailed in our house, although we knew deep down that it was really, really getting from bad to worse.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The other Jewish families, the other four Jewish families who lived in Gemunden, their situation got so bad that eventually, they all moved in to our house with us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So by that time, by the end of 1939, the middle of 1939, I believe there were approximately 12 or 13 people living in our house.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We all shared the same problems.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We had the same experiences, more or less.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I believe it was-- was a tremendous support.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We were a tremendous support for each other, because there was no way out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "There was just no way out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By that time, my father had abandoned the idea that Hitler wouldn't last very long, which he always was proclaiming through 1934, and '35, and '36.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, he had been exposed to the terrible, terrible physical tyranny in November the 9th night that he-- he just said, well, we just have to wait and see what's happening, you know?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had very little contact with Jewish agencies in Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our life was miserable.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
